text: James H. Higgins was an American Democratic Party politician who served as governor of Rhode Island from 1907 to 1909. During his time as governor a number of labor laws were introduced.Title: November 1909 : Bulletin of the United States Bureau of Labor, No. 85, Volume XIX, P.761-763 ==References== Category:Democratic Party (United States) politicians Category:Governors of Rhode Island
title: James H. Higgins
